17/10/2007
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The leaders of BiH's two entities and the central government signed an agreement Tuesday (October 16) aimed at fixing the country's ailing economy. BiH Prime Minister Nikola Spiric, the prime ministers of the Federation of BiH and Republika Srpska -- Nedzad Brankovic and Milorad Dodik -- and Brcko Mayor Mirsad Djapo adopted a document listing the most urgent economic reforms. Their Platform of Action cites attracting investment, boosting employment and raising living standards as the most important and immediate challenges for the three governments. (DPA - 16/10/07)
